article_metadata.description: More than 150,000 Ohioans will be put back on Medicaid under a settlement of a lawsuit against the state. Details of the agreement were released today, about a week after the settlement was announced. The dispute centered on how the Ohio Department of Medicaid conducted an annual process to determine whether beneficiaries remain eligible for health coverage.
